<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/2f9d9920e611b8d99a98c1f2f26d8da9.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 3 and c = 10. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>9.5</li><li>17.5</li><li>72.5</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{100}={9}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{100}-{9}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{91}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{91}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9.5393920141695}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9.5}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{10}}\right)}}}\approx{17.457603123722}\approx{17.5}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{10}}\right)}}}\approx{72.542396876278}\approx{72.5}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

